    "type": "message",
    "text": "I hate to be the cold splash of reality, but some people don't pay for content. Over the last 15 years, sales of my labeling software to China exactly equal the sales to the tiny country of New Caledonia. I defy you to locate New Caledonia on a world map. Honesty is not evenly distributed. That is a per capita sales ratio of around 5000:1. So i think that China could stand some improvement in terms of their attitude towards paying for intellectual property.",
